When would you want to use a remote repository rather than keeping all your work
local?

    By having your projects saved in a remote repository rather than a local machine you don't need to worry about sudden lose of your project

Why might you want to always pull changes manually rather than having Git
automatically stay up-to-date with your remote repository?

    having your project stay updated automatically can cause issues if their are contributors that made changes that you don't want

Describe the differences between forks, clones, and branches.  When would you
use one instead of another?

    the difference between a fork and a clone is that a fork is a clone of someones repository to your repository to make changes on your own without effecting their repository. A branch is what you create when you are wanting to change somthing in your project and you don't want to change your core code

